item.description:
&ldquo;Aiiiiyaaaa! Jacky! You did not install Ruuuubyyy. You need that to write your blog.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I already install Ruby, uncle, but it still does not work. rake generate creates empty HTML file! Look, it&rsquo;s broken!&rdquo;
1 2 3  &gt;rake generate Generating... C:/Ruby200-x64/lib/ruby/gems/2.0.0/gems/posix-spawn-0.3.8/lib/posix/spawn.rb:162: warning: cannot close fd before spawn &#39;which&#39; is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.   Swat!
&ldquo;Ow! What was dat for?

Maybe I&rsquo;ll manage to keep a somewhat OK journal if I write it on my blog&hellip;
Dear journal-that-everybody-can-read,
Today we finally got internet in our apartment, which I may explain another time. A guy showed up at 9 o&rsquo;clock sharp and installed it, after which I had to call the support center for help because their installation disk didn&rsquo;t work (because I have English Windows?). The internet is blazing fast, and now I can work on online classes without taking a trip to Erika&rsquo;s work.
